-- Ex-divs to take up to 11.1 points off FTSE 100 on Aug. 20
-- 
-- Mon Aug 18, 2014 07:12AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, Aug 18 (Reuters) - The following FTSE 100 <.FTSE> companies will go ex-dividend on Wednesday, after which investors will no longer qualify for the latest dividend payout.

According to Reuters calculations at current market prices, the effect of  the resulting adjustment to prices by market-makers would take up to 11.09 points off the index. COMPANY   (RIC)  DIVIDENDMAXMIN   (pence) IMPACT IMPACT  British American  <BATS.L> 52.78 3.9483 3.5534  Tobacco   Carnival  <CCL.L>  27.78 (U.S. cents)0.1199 0.1079  Hammerson <HMSO.L>  8.8  0.2465 0.1972  HSBC Holdings <HSBA.L> 11.11 (U.S. cents)5.0138   InterContinental  <IHG.L>  16.44 0.1539 0.1385  Hotels Group  Mondi <MNDI.L> 14.7 (euro cents) 0.1709 0.1538  Prudential<PRU.L>  12.43 1.2560 1.1304  Rexam <REX.L>   6.44 0.1787 0.1608  Among FTSE 250 <.FTMC> companies going ex-dividend are:COMPANY(RIC)DIVIDEND